<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q13_v5" title="Q13_v5" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>Se registra el siguiente reajuste de arriendo mensual:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Arriendo mensual actual: $210</li>
      <li>Descripción del cambio: el arriendo actual es un 40% mayor que el arriendo original.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>¿Cuál de las siguientes expresiones numéricas permite calcular el valor del arriendo mensual original?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>210</m:mn>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mn>40</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Esta expresión da 210 − 40 = 170, pero 170 no cumple que 210 sea un 40% mayor que ese valor. Si el original fuera 170, entonces aumentar 40% da 170 × 1,4 = 238, no 210.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>210</m:mn>
            <m:mo>·</m:mo>
            <m:mn>100</m:mn>
            <m:mo>/</m:mo>
            <m:mn>140</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Si el arriendo actual es un 40% mayor que el original, entonces 210 representa el 140% del valor original. Por eso el original se calcula como 210 × 100 / 140 = 150. Además, 150 × 1,4 = 210.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>210</m:mn>
            <m:mo>+</m:mo>
            <m:mn>40</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Esta expresión da 210 + 40 = 250, pero 250 no puede ser el arriendo original, porque el actual debe ser mayor que el original. Además, 250 × 1,4 = 350, no 210.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>210</m:mn>
            <m:mo>·</m:mo>
            <m:mn>140</m:mn>
            <m:mo>/</m:mo>
            <m:mn>100</m:mn>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Esta expresión da 210 × 140 / 100 = 294. Ese cálculo aumenta 210 en 40%, pero 210 ya es el arriendo actual. El problema pide encontrar el original, así que se debe deshacer el aumento, no volver a aumentarlo.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Interpretar la información del enunciado</strong></p>
            <p>El arriendo actual es $210 y es un 40% mayor que el arriendo original.</p>
            <p>Eso significa que el valor actual corresponde al 140% del valor original.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Relacionar porcentaje y valor</strong></p>
            <p>Si llamamos original al arriendo inicial, entonces:</p>
            <p>140% del original = 210.</p>
            <p>En porcentaje, 140% = 140/100 = 1,4.</p>
            <p>Entonces:</p>
            <p>original × 1,4 = 210.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Despejar el valor original</strong></p>
            <p>Para obtener el original, dividimos por 1,4:</p>
            <p>original = 210 / 1,4.</p>
            <p>Equivalentemente:</p>
            <p>original = 210 × 100 / 140.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Calcular</strong></p>
            <p>210 × 100 / 140 = 21 000 / 140 = 150.</p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, el arriendo mensual original era $150.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Verificar</strong></p>
            <p>El 40% de 150 es 60.</p>
            <p>Entonces 150 + 60 = 210.</p>
            <p>La verificación coincide con el enunciado.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La expresión correcta es 210 · 100 / 140, que corresponde a la alternativa B.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>